(103, '14. Emotional withdrawal [Unspontaneous relations to examiner, lack of peer interaction, hypoactivity]', 'Not at all,Occasionally is unresponsive; sometimes refuses peer interactions,Frequently unresponsive; lacks peer interaction; hypoactive. Interferes with relationships.,Constantly oblivious to those around. Preoccupied facial expressions; does not respond to questions or look at the interviewer.', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
(104, '15. Blunt Affect [Deficient emotional expression, blankness, flatness of affect.]', 'Not at all or explainable by depressed mood,Some flattening of affect. Occasionally shows emotional response during interview (smiles; laughs; tearful),Considerable flattening. Frequently the client does not show emotional response (does not smile; laugh; look; cry).,Constantly flat. The client does not show emotional response (does not smile; laugh; look; cry).', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
(105, '16. Tensions [Nervousness, fidgetiness, nervous movements of hands or feet]', 'Not at all,Occasionally feels nervous or fidgets. Can be relaxed or reassured.,Most days/time feels nervous/fidgety.,Pervasive and extreme nervousness; fidgeting; nervous movements of hands/feet.', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
(106, '17. Anxiety [Clinging behavior, separation anxiety, preoccupation with anxiety topics, fears, or phobias]', 'Not at all,Occasionally worries (at least three times a week) about anticipated/current events. separation; fears; or phobias. Worries appear excessive for the situation,Most days/times worries about at least two life circumstances; or anticipated/current events.,Pervasive and extreme worry about most everything real or imagined.', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
(107, '18. Sleep Difficulties [Inability to fall asleep, intermittent awakening, shortened sleep time]', 'Not at all,Some difficulty (at least 1-hour initial; no middle or terminal insomnia),Definitely has difficulty (at least 2 hours initial insomnia; any middle; or terminal lasting up to 1/2 1 hour). Feelings of unrestorative sleep; evidence or mild circadian reversal,Claims to never sleep. feels exhausted the rest of the day; or severe circadian reversal.', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
(108, '19. Disorientation [Confusion over persons, places, or things]', 'Not at all,Occasionally appears confused or puzzled. Easily reacquainted with surrounding when prompted,Frequently appears puzzled; confused; baffled regarding familiar surroundings; people; or things,Constantly confused; Perplexed.', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
(109, '20. Speech Deviance [Inferior level of speech development, underdeveloped vocabulary, mispronunciations]', 'Not at all,Occasional instances of distorted and idiosyncratic speech. Little impairment of understandability.,Frequent instances with definite impairment in understandability.,Constant speech distortion; almost incomprehensible.', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
(110, '21. Stereotypy [Rhythmic, repetitive, manneristic movements or posture]', 'Not at all,Occasionally displays rhythmic; repetitive; manneristic movements or posture.,Frequent rhythmic; repetitive; manneristic movements or posture.,Most of the time (>50%) displays rhythmic; repetitive; manneristic movement/posture.', 'Child Psychiatry', 'Active', '2023-07-22 05:13:20', '2023-07-22 05:13:20'),
